<p>Among the 26 PMAs approved by the US Center for Devices and Radiological Health in fiscal 1994 were four "firsts" for the US market. They include a ventricular assist device to serve as a bridge to cardiac transplantation (Thermo Cardiosystem's HeartMate); a contrast agent for use in ultrasound imaging of the heart for wall motion studies (Molecular Biosystems' Albunex); the use of the <strong>[C#198601109:Hybritech]</strong> Tandem PSA Assay for prostate cancer screening; and a stent for initial treatment of symptomatic, short lesions in large coronary arteries (Johnson & Johnson's Palmaz-Schatz).</p>
